QUIVERING PALM			TYPE:Focus.Uncommon.Monk.Incapacitation.Necromancy																																																DURATION:1 month									DESC:Make a melee unarmed Strike. If you hit and the target is alive, anytime during the duration, you can spend a single action, which has the auditory and concentrate traits, to speak a word of death that could instantly slay it. The target must attempt a Fortitude save.	DESC:&nl;Critical Success The target survives, the spell ends, and the target is then temporarily immune for 24 hours.	DESC:&nl;Success The target is stunned 1 and takes 40 damage, the spell ends, and the target is then temporarily immune for 24 hours.	DESC:&nl;Failure The target is stunned 3 and takes 80 damage. The spell's duration continues, but the target is then temporarily immune for 24 hours against being killed by quivering palm.	DESC:&nl;Critical Failure The target dies. If you cast quivering palm again, the effects of any quivering palm you had previously cast end.	DESC:&nl;Heightened (+1) The damage increases by 10 on a failure, or 5 on a success.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												INFO:FocusLevel|8	INFO:Casting|somatic, verbal	INFO:SavingThrow|Fortitude
RAISE DEAD				TYPE:Spell.Uncommon.Healing.Necromancy.Divine								RANGE:10 feet															TARGETAREA:one dead creature of level 13 or lower																											DESC:You attempt to call forth the dead creature's soul, requiring the creature's body to be present and relatively intact. The creature must have died within the past 3 days. If Pharasma has decided that the creature's time has come (at the GM's discretion), or if the creature doesn't wish to return to life, this spell automatically fails, but the diamonds aren't consumed in the casting. If the spell is successful, the creature returns to life with 1 Hit Point, no spells prepared or spell slots available, no points in any pools or any other daily resources, and still with any long-term debilitations of the old body. The time spent in the Boneyard leaves the target temporarily debilitated, making it clumsy 2, drained 2, and enfeebled 2 for 1 week; these conditions can't be removed or reduced by any means until the week has passed. The creature is also permanently changed by its time in the afterlife, such as a slight personality shift, a streak of white in the hair, or a strange new birthmark.	DESC:&nl;Heightened (7th) The maximum level of the target increases to 15. The cost increases to the target's level (minimum 1) Ã- 400 gp.	DESC:&nl;Heightened (8th) The maximum level the target increases to 17. The cost increases to the target's level (minimum 1) Ã- 800 gp.	DESC:&nl;Heightened (9th) The maximum level of the target increases to 19. The cost increases to the target's level (minimum 1) Ã- 1,600 gp.	DESC:&nl;Heightened (10th) The maximum level the target increases to 21. The cost increases to the target's level (minimum 1) Ã- 3,200 gp.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				INFO:SpellLevel|6	INFO:Casting|10 minutes (material, somatic, verbal)	INFO:Cost|diamonds worth a total value of the target's level (minimum 1) Ã- 200 gp
RAY OF ENFEEBLEMENT		TYPE:Spell.Attack.Necromancy.Arcane.Divine.Occult							RANGE:30 feet															TARGETAREA:one creature																					DURATION:1 minute									DESC:A ray with the power to sap a foe's strength flashes from your hand. Attempt a ranged spell attack against the target. If you succeed, that creature attempts a Fortitude save in order to determine the spell's effect. If you critically succeed on your attack roll, use the outcome for one degree of success worse than the result of its save.	DESC:&nl;Critical Success The target is unaffected.	DESC:&nl;Success The target becomes enfeebled 1.	DESC:&nl;Failure The target becomes enfeebled 2.	DESC:&nl;Critical Failure The target becomes enfeebled 3.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													INFO:SpellLevel|1	INFO:Casting|somatic, verbal
